Daniela MÃ¼ller (born 10 July 1957 in Aschaffenburg, Germany) is a German theologian and church historian, who works in the Netherlands since 2007 and who holds the chair of Church History/History of Christianity and Canon Law at the Radboud University in Nijmegen. She has numerous publications on the subjects heresy and dissidents, and is the editor of the in 2014 initiated book series Christentum und Dissidenz.
